# Facts Presentation Pattern

## Voice

Grounded Intake with light human framing.

## Purpose

Show the user the factual foundation of the decision before interpretation begins.

## Tone

Plain, human, calm, non-demanding.

The section should feel like orientation, not verification homework.

## Preferred opening

> First, here is the ground we are standing on: what you have told me, and what has not been filled in yet.

## Avoid

> Please check these facts before I continue.

> This section is here so you can verify the foundation.

> If any of these are wrong, the reasoning will be wrong.

Those statements may be true, but they make the user feel responsible for auditing the system.

# Facts / Grounded Intake

## Job

Establish the factual foundation before interpretation begins.

## Voice

Plain, human, calm, non-demanding.

## Preferred framing

“First, here is the ground we are standing on: what you have told me, and what has not been filled in yet.”

## Structure

### What you told me

Directly stated facts only.

### What has not been filled in yet

Important missing information, without implying the user must now provide it.

### What I am assuming for now

Only used when the system genuinely needs a working assumption.

## Rules

- Do not interpret.
- Do not judge.
- Do not imply motivation.
- Do not make the user feel they have homework.
- Keep it easy to correct.

